parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leak and Valve Cover Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause damage to the catalytic converter, leading to a fire hazard, and valve cover failure can cause engine performance issues and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: Oil leaking onto the valve cover
oil dripping onto the catalytic converter
clutch pedal sticking to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Exhaust Manifold Failure and Heat Shield Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the exhaust manifold can cause damage to surrounding components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing a fire hazard.
Failure to properly notify vehicle owners of recalls and inadequate repair work can lead to continued safety risks and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: refusal to reimburse for previous repairs
and failure to properly diagnose and repair issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Antifreeze leaks can cause engine damage and potentially lead to overheating, which can cause accidents.
The failure of the headlight mechanism can cause reduced visibility, especially at night, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights will not raise or lower

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of rear brakes can lead to reduced stopping power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: rear brakes need to be replaced prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of rear brake assembly components can cause reduced stopping power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: split brake pad on the left rear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of bolts from the rear caliper, damaged rim, and faulty emergency brake bracket pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents. The split brake pad on the left rear can cause uneven brake wear, further compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: grinding or screeching noise when applying brakes
vibration or pulling to one side when braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake pad can cause uneven brake wear, reduced braking performance, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when applying brakes
vibration or pulling to one side when braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake bracket pads can cause the parking brake to malfunction, leading to unintended vehicle movement, accidents, or rollaways.
symptoms: Parking brake does not engage or disengage properly
